HEADWORD: Elucidate
<hw>E*lu"ci*date</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Elucidated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Elucidating</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[LL.
<ets>elucidatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>elucidare</ets>; <ets>e</ets> +
<ets>lucidus</ets> full of light, clear. See <er>Lucid</er>.]</ety>
<def>To make clear or manifest; to render more intelligible; to
illustrate; <as>as, an example will <ex>elucidate</ex> the
subject</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Elucidation</ent>⟦br⟧
